covid<-read.csv(file = 'covid_week.csv')
str(covid)
## 'data.frame':    31 obs. of  2 variables:
##  $ week : chr  "2020-01-20" "2020-01-27" "2020-02-03" "2020-02-10" ...
##  $ count: int  3 12 12 2 584 3128 3279 854 725 700 ...
covid$cumsum<-cumsum(covid$count)
str(covid)
## 'data.frame':    31 obs. of  3 variables:
##  $ week  : chr  "2020-01-20" "2020-01-27" "2020-02-03" "2020-02-10" ...
##  $ count : int  3 12 12 2 584 3128 3279 854 725 700 ...
##  $ cumsum: int  3 15 27 29 613 3741 7020 7874 8599 9299 ...
top10<-genie %>% filter( %in% 1:10)
t<-top10 %>% group_by() %>% summarise(=sum())

g<-ggplot(t)+geom_line(aes(x=,y=,color=''),color='darkgreen')

covid$week<-as.Date(covid$week)
g1<-g+geom_line(data = covid,aes(x=week,y=cumsum*50000,color='cumsum*50000'),color='red')

g2<-g1+scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~./50000, name = ''))+
  scale_color_discrete(name = "color", labels = c("", ""))+
  theme_light()+
  theme(axis.line.y.right = element_line(colour = 'red'),
        axis.line.y.left = element_line(colour = 'darkgreen'))
